that was engineered, and I believe we can reach parity.

482
00:26:10,858 --> 00:26:12,198
Well, how can we do that?

483
00:26:12,559 --> 00:26:14,900
Well, first, I think we need to clear away the myths.

484
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:19,621
and one of the big myths I often hear is that girls are not good at maths and IT,

485
00:26:20,121 --> 00:26:21,801
and that is simply not true.

486
00:26:21,901 --> 00:26:25,662
In fact, many studies show that girls are good at maths and IT,

487
00:26:26,022 --> 00:26:28,142
and unless they're told that they're not,

488
00:26:28,602 --> 00:26:30,503
and then they'll live down to it,

489
00:26:30,623 --> 00:26:32,843
and that works the same with boys, by the way.

490
00:26:33,983 --> 00:26:38,704
There was also a fantastic study done by Science Foundation Ireland

491
00:26:38,744 --> 00:26:42,685
that talked about how important the message is coming from parents.

492
00:26:42,765 --> 00:26:43,165
In fact...

493
00:26:44,046 --> 00:26:48,369
A kid's mother is the most important influencer

494
00:26:48,589 --> 00:26:50,890
of their children's future career choices.

495
00:26:51,351 --> 00:26:53,832
So if mothers say, absolutely, you would be great at this,

496
00:26:54,132 --> 00:26:55,393
kids tend to follow that.

497
00:26:55,533 --> 00:26:59,516
And so educating parents as well is incredibly important

498
00:27:00,176 --> 00:27:03,098
because they can influence their children's decisions

499
00:27:03,158 --> 00:27:04,239
more than anything else.

500
00:27:05,060 --> 00:27:07,341
And we all know that it must change.

501
00:27:07,962 --> 00:27:11,323
Women were the original computers, quite literally.

502
00:27:11,643 --> 00:27:13,064
We created code.

503
00:27:13,524 --> 00:27:15,364
We created programming languages.

504
00:27:15,765 --> 00:27:16,905
We built the machines.

505
00:27:17,425 --> 00:27:20,106
We put a man on the moon, for God's sakes,

506
00:27:20,226 --> 00:27:23,848
and just to be petty, we also built the man

507
00:27:23,888 --> 00:27:25,448
who got put on the moon as well.

508
00:27:26,109 --> 00:27:30,652
And as much as I'm saying this, this is about diversity and it is not at all about exclusion.

509
00:27:30,832 --> 00:27:37,837
It's important for us to get to equal because there are loads of studies that show

510
00:27:38,217 --> 00:27:43,981
that diverse teams make better games and diverse teams make for better educational environments.

511
00:27:44,382 --> 00:27:48,645
So we need to clear away the barriers for what's keeping people out of, let's say,

512
00:27:48,665 --> 00:27:51,827
the other side of the room. And it's also the business case.

513
00:27:53,088 --> 00:27:56,790
Even more than that, companies need to have more workers.

514
00:27:56,870 --> 00:27:59,331
Like this might be fine now, but as an industry,

515
00:27:59,391 --> 00:28:03,133
we are growing and we need to fill many more chairs.

516
00:28:03,373 --> 00:28:04,554
And in part to do this,

517
00:28:04,634 --> 00:28:06,975
I also think we need to change the marketing.

518
00:28:07,435 --> 00:28:10,877
So I decided to get in my,

519
00:28:11,197 --> 00:28:13,578
this free time that I fantasize that I sometimes have,

520
00:28:13,678 --> 00:28:16,079
I decided to get back into seed.

521
00:28:16,900 --> 00:28:18,960
And so I found a C programming tutorial.

522
00:28:19,100 --> 00:28:21,281
And this was the first and most recommended one.

523
00:28:21,301 --> 00:28:22,782
And this is the very first thing I see.

524
00:28:22,902 --> 00:28:25,882
So I imagine just rocking this thing up to my daughters

525
00:28:25,942 --> 00:28:27,563
and them looking at this guy going like,

526
00:28:27,623 --> 00:28:29,864
I'm old and I'm white.

527
00:28:30,544 --> 00:28:33,165
And don't you wanna be like me, right?

528
00:28:33,265 --> 00:28:35,925
You know, like if we're looking for equality and diversity,

529
00:28:35,965 --> 00:28:37,606
I think that there's way better ways to sell it.

530
00:28:37,646 --> 00:28:39,747
Like, why not having Margaret Hamilton there?

531
00:28:39,847 --> 00:28:41,027
Like, I love this.

532
00:28:41,067 --> 00:28:42,787
You know, here's a woman who put man on the moon.

533
00:28:42,827 --> 00:28:43,548
Like, let's do it.

534
00:28:44,068 --> 00:28:47,732
And then I remember this advertisement, which is currently my all-time favorite.

535
00:28:47,752 --> 00:28:50,856
This comes from 2011. So this is a company that was looking for programmers.

536
00:28:51,877 --> 00:28:56,642
And this was their ad campaign. So you would be, if you, if you signed up and you were hired,

537
00:28:56,682 --> 00:29:00,987
you would get a tux, which I thought maybe I could rock the tux, but then you would also get

538
00:29:01,448 --> 00:29:03,970
cologne, which was sex panther cologne.

539
00:29:05,119 --> 00:29:05,880
Which, okay.

540
00:29:06,281 --> 00:29:08,183
And then this is the one where I drew the line,

541
00:29:08,223 --> 00:29:10,165
like, I don't want their beard grooming oil.

542
00:29:10,245 --> 00:29:10,986
That's what that was.

543
00:29:11,206 --> 00:29:14,790
Cigars, whiskey, bacon-wrapped money, fine.

544
00:29:15,010 --> 00:29:16,231
Beard grooming oil, no.

545
00:29:16,251 --> 00:29:19,214
Right, like it just, it doesn't say that you belong.

546
00:29:19,354 --> 00:29:22,077
And so I think it's important that we change the message.

547
00:29:23,018 --> 00:29:25,401
I sometimes think about doing something like having

548
00:29:25,481 --> 00:29:27,122
an exceptional summer camp

549
00:29:27,803 --> 00:29:29,665
or summer camp for exceptional coders,

550
00:29:29,985 --> 00:29:32,387
and just constantly telling girls that,

551
00:29:32,467 --> 00:29:35,010
girls are natural coders and IT is for girls,

552
00:29:35,090 --> 00:29:37,452
and overwhelming them with this message.

553
00:29:37,812 --> 00:29:40,455
Not because I just want to say it and hammer it home,

554
00:29:40,735 --> 00:29:42,897
but actually because it's true,

555
00:29:42,937 --> 00:29:44,278
it is really true.

556
00:29:44,799 --> 00:29:49,124
There were times in my life where I was told that I was no good.

557
00:29:49,164 --> 00:29:51,467
I was told by a teacher that I wouldn't amount to anything.

558
00:29:52,187 --> 00:29:54,050
I was told that I would live in the worst part of town.

559
00:29:54,090 --> 00:29:57,474
I was told I had no chance of getting into a college of my choice.

560
00:29:58,034 --> 00:29:58,715
And I was told

561
00:29:59,769 --> 00:30:03,310
not to make the games that ended up being part of the reason that I won a BAFTA.

562
00:30:04,731 --> 00:30:09,052
And what if I believed all that, right? Like, you know, the good news is, is that I'm a fighter.

563
00:30:09,813 --> 00:30:14,034
And I wrote three books and I made those games and I got into that college and I live in Galway,

564
00:30:14,054 --> 00:30:17,975
which is a long way from where I thought those people, those people thought I would end up.

565
00:30:18,275 --> 00:30:22,357
And I'm grateful for my life and I'm grateful that I didn't listen. You know, but it's sometimes

566
00:30:22,417 --> 00:30:28,419
like I'm not a fighter. And sometimes I believe the shit that I hear. And I wonder how many girls

567
00:30:29,139 --> 00:30:35,592
we've lost to those messages that are just obviously not true. I mean, ultimately, game dev is for everyone.

568
00:30:37,235 --> 00:30:42,439
and code is for everyone. And I want anybody who wants in these doors to come on in and see people

569
00:30:42,499 --> 00:30:46,622
who look like them, you know, whether they're school kids or just entry level into the job

570
00:30:46,662 --> 00:30:51,866
or they're lead coders or, you know, they've gone up to the CTO level. Like, I want to build the

571
00:30:51,906 --> 00:30:56,909
ladder for those who come after us to show them where to go so that when we look at an image like

572
00:30:56,949 --> 00:31:02,273
this, you know, we don't think like, oh, my goodness, it's girls coding. You know, we look

573
00:31:02,293 --> 00:31:06,476
at this as just a completely normal thing. Like, yeah, there's some kids making some games.

574
00:31:07,816 --> 00:31:10,146
I want everybody to feel welcome in this industry.

575
00:31:10,528 --> 00:31:10,830
Thank you.

